                    p.caption Lost in transition
                    img.full-width(src="../img/kinetic-challenge3.webp", alt="Typography")
                    p.caption Drafting on paper helped me develop the idea of a wave sweeping up as a transition.

                    p Another challenge was ensuring the elements moved as intended while keeping timing in mind. For example, animating the walking crab involved rotating and positioning each leg individually, and the movement needed to be large enough to be visible, given the small size of the legs on screen. 
                    img.full-width(src="../img/kinetic-challenge4.webp", alt="Typography")
                    p.caption Controlling the keyframes for animating crab legs

                    p Despite these challenges, this project strengthened my understanding of animation principles. I gained hands-on experience using After Effects, particularly in working with 3D layers, camera movements, and keyframe adjustments. Moving forward, I plan to explore more complex animations and transitions, further refining both my technical and conceptual skills.

